experiences.introduction: Devil’s Peak used to be an essential passage to Victoria Harbour in the 20th century. A 207-degree view of the harbour awaits you at the trenches. You can spot some historical remnants here.
experiences.name: Devil's Peak

experiences.introduction: Dragon’s Back offers a beginner-friendly hike with not-so-hilly and easy access to some of the most Insta-worthy views. End your hike by Shek O Village’s beach.
experiences.name: Dragon's Back

experiences.introduction: Jardine’s Lookout Hike proves that you don’t have to hike far to enjoy a beautiful view of the city. This short trail allows you to appreciate a relaxing sunset view with little crowd.
experiences.name: Jardine's Lookout Hike

experiences.introduction: Lamma Island Hike’s trail will take you to Hung Shing Yeh Beach where you can enjoy the sun and the white sand. Move on to the island’s Family Trail and be rewarded with a splendid view.
experiences.name: Lamma Island Hike

experiences.introduction: If you’re just starting to hike, consider Lion Rock. With a 495-metre climb, reaching the pinnacle is an achievement in itself because it is one of Hong Kong’s highest peaks.
experiences.name: Lion Rock

experiences.introduction: Hike on a sunny day at Sharp Peak, one of the Sai Kung region’s highest points. There’s no break in incline as you go straight up from the beach but the coastal views from atop are worth it
experiences.name: Sharp Peak

experiences.introduction: Although it’s called Suicide Cliff, it’s no place for tragedy. The viewpoints in this trail are very precarious so be careful! Snap your best pose here with Kowloon in the background.
experiences.name: Suicide Cliff

experiences.introduction: Sunset Peak hike has one of the best viewpoints for sunsets. Start by climbing the long set of stairs that leads to a trail and into the forest. Emerge to the hilltop and you’ll reach the peak.
experiences.name: Sunset Peak

experiences.introduction: Taking The Peak hike will reward you with a photo op with Victoria Harbour and HK's skyscrapers as backdrops. The hike itself is easy and you'll even see children and the elderly along the trail.
experiences.name: The Peak

experiences.introduction: Test your limits at The Twins’ 4.8-kilometre trail —one of the most challenging hikes in Hong Kong. The 1,200-step climb to the peak will surely work your glutes and legs to the max!
experiences.name: The Twins

experiences.introduction: Hailed as the hardest hike in Hong Kong, West Dog’s Teeth Ridge is an 850-metre incline wherein you’ll have to boulder and scramble to reach the ridge’s end. At the end of this trail is Lantau Peak.
experiences.name: West Dog’s Teeth Hike

experiences.introduction: 50% off selected beer, cocktails and win, with complimentary antipasti. Happy Hour! from 3pm - 7pm daily.
experiences.name: 208 Duecento Otto

experiences.introduction: Armoury is a great spot for post work drinks with plenty of outdoor seating. Enjoy $50 cocktails every single day from 3pm - 8pm.
experiences.name: Armoury

experiences.introduction: Get bubbly with $38 glasses of wine and prosecco. Happy Hour! from 3pm - 8pm daily.
experiences.name: Ask for Alonzo

experiences.introduction: Buy one, get one free on selected wines, beers and cocktails between 4pm-7pm daily.
experiences.name: Bizou

experiences.introduction: This Peel Street staple does $40 beers and wine from 3pm-10pm Monday to Saturday. It doesn't get cheaper than this - except for the 7/11 down the road ;)
experiences.name: Chi Chi Cham

experiences.introduction: Free-flow beer, wings and fries for $108. This is definitely one of the craziest deals we've seen in Soho. Weekdays from 5pm-7pm.
experiences.name: Finis

experiences.introduction: One of our favourites, this gem in Sai Ying Pun does $40 wines, spirits and cocktails from 3pm-7pm on weekdays and 4pm-6pm on weekends.
experiences.name: Flying Pig

experiences.introduction: $25 drinks evey day from 4pm-7pm. Ocean views complimentary. Need we say more?
experiences.name: Hemingways

experiences.introduction: Ichu offers some mean Peruvian food alongside $50 house spirits and cocktails. Happy Hour! from 3pm-6pm on weekdays only.
experiences.name: Ichu Terraza

experiences.introduction: Looking for a loooong Happy Hour with good food? Mr. Wolf does beers, wines, and cocktails from $45 onwards from 3pm to 9pm every day. Insider tip: Don't miss their chicken tikka
experiences.name: Mr Wolf

experiences.introduction: A classy Spanish-style gin bar, Optimist does selected wines, beers and spirits for $48 every day from 3pm - 7.30pm.
experiences.name: Optimist

experiences.introduction: Free flow wine? We hear you. $350 pp for 2 hours, 12pm-7pm Monday through Saturday.
experiences.name: PIIN Wine Restaurant

experiences.introduction: Enjoy drinks at half price every day from 3pm-6pm
experiences.name: Scarlett Cafe and Wine Bar

experiences.introduction: Don't look further if you plan to start drinking early. Buy one, get one free on beers and wines and special prices on cocktails. Every day from 12pm-9pm.
experiences.name: Tai Lung Fung

experiences.introduction: Fancy some tacos and tequila in TST? Check out TJ's for $40 margaritas and beers every day from 3pm-9pm.
experiences.name: Tequila Jack's

experiences.introduction: Unwind and delight in The Shady Acres' happy hour from 11PM to 1AM daily with your friends! The pub's No Sleep 'Till Pilsner, Shady x Brooklyn is a must-try.
experiences.name: The Shady Acres

experiences.introduction: Some of the best cocktails in town with super friendly bartenders. $50 cocktails every day from 6pm-9pm.
experiences.name: Varga Lounge

collection_detail.introduction: Our favourite Happy Hour spots in town!
collection_detail.name: Happy Hour!

experiences.introduction: Who says dates can’t be sweeter? You and your date can learn how to make wagashi, a traditional Japanese sweet, at ABC Cooking Studio. Each class is maxed at four people so you have plenty of support.
experiences.name: ABC Cooking Studio - Central

experiences.introduction: Who says dates can’t be sweeter? You and your date can learn how to make wagashi, a traditional Japanese sweet, at ABC Cooking Studio. Each class is maxed at four people so you have plenty of support.
experiences.name: ABC Cooking Studio - Tsim Sha Tsui

experiences.introduction: Who says dates can’t be sweeter? You and your date can learn how to make wagashi, a traditional Japanese sweet, at ABC Cooking Studio. Each class is maxed at four people so you have plenty of support.
experiences.name: ABC Cooking Studio - Taikoo Shing

experiences.introduction: Whether you and your partner are beginners or experienced in creating art, try Art Loft’s freestyle painting jam. Each session lasts for 2 hours. All art materials provided!
experiences.name: Art Loft

experiences.introduction: Take the time off and create art together with your significant other here at Art Roof Top. Its workshops for adults include life drawing, painting portrait, still life, plein air, and more.
experiences.name: Art Roof Top

experiences.introduction: If you and your date are into arts, head over to Artjammning and let your creativity flow! With high-quality canvasses and free-flow acrylics, you won't run out of ideas.
experiences.name: Artjamming

experiences.introduction: Attend a fun art class at Banana Art Club with your date. Here, art instructions are customised for all ages and abilities. The best part? You can learn together anywhere that’s convenient for you.
experiences.name: Banana Art Club

experiences.introduction: A date isn't complete without food, so spice it up through a memorable culinary experience with BiteUnite. From baking floral cookies and mooncakes to cooking Thai cuisine, BiteUnite has it all!
experiences.name: BiteUnite

experiences.introduction: Learn calligraphy at Bonart Workshops and find yourself and your date exchanging beautifully penned love notes later on! Bonart’s copperplate calligraphy workshops include a starter kit.
experiences.name: Bonart Workshops

experiences.introduction: Learn art while enjoying a 270-degree view of Hong Kong’s streets at Choco L'ART Studio. You and your date can bring your own food and drinks free of charge. Sounds like a perfect date.
experiences.name: Choco L'ART Studio

experiences.introduction: PERMANENTLY CLOSED
experiences.name: Fungus Workshop

experiences.introduction: Creating a couple cup isn't a bad idea, so head over to Glazden for a cup making experience! Here, you'll learn about glass blowing and work with patterns and colours to design your own cup.
experiences.name: Glazden

experiences.introduction: Add a fun twist to your date night by learning pottery at Half Corner Studio. Here, beginners can learn clay preparation and hand-building techniques. Regular and floating classes are available.
experiences.name: Half Corner Studio

experiences.introduction: Impress your significant other by making plum blossom-shaped or goldfish-shaped dumplings learned from Hong Kong New Oriental Culinary Art. The school also offers baking and other cooking classes.
experiences.name: Hong Kong New Oriental Culinary Art

experiences.introduction: What's sweeter than bringing your date to Lazy Baking Studio to craft confections together? Here, you will be guided through baking, layering, creaming, and adding finishing touches.
experiences.name: Lazy Baking Studio

experiences.introduction: Learning hands-on Chinese cuisine at Martha Sherpa's Cooking Classes can be an incredible bonding experience for couples. The school also teaches how to cook vegetarian, Thai, and other dishes.
experiences.name: Martha Sherpa's Cooking Classes

experiences.introduction: Nothing more special than something that's handmade with love. At Motto, you will learn how to make leather wallets, belts, handbags, and more. Bring your date too and make this a bonding!
experiences.name: Motto

experiences.introduction: Try something new with your date this weekend by attending Studio 83’s acrylic and oil class. If you need a space for art creation, the studio has DIY painting sessions available.
experiences.name: Studio 83

experiences.introduction: Immerse in a memorable creative glassmaking experience at Studio Glass. Here, you can learn how to make ornaments, utensils, and other gifts. A perfect way to create your first gift made with glass!
experiences.name: Studio Glass

experiences.introduction: Bake up a little romance by bringing your date at The Little Kitchen Cookery Studio to learn how to create Instagrammable desserts and cakes. You can also learn other savoury dishes here upon request.
experiences.name: The Little Kitchen Cookery Studio

experiences.introduction: Give your date night a different spin by attending Useless Studio’s pottery classes. The studio also offers wheel throwing, ceramic art courses, and other pottery sessions.
experiences.name: Useless Studio

experiences.introduction: Going to a date but you have no one to look after your pets at home? Bring them to Quarry Bay Promenade Pet Garden. There's a park near this 1.8km-waterfront, perfect for strolling with your date!
experiences.name: Quarry Bay Promenade Pet Garden

collection_detail.introduction: There’s an art to making happy memories!
collection_detail.name: Creative Dates

experiences.introduction: Dr. Fern's Gin Parlour is a great hideaway after a long day. The bar creates custom cocktails for everyone which you can enjoy with bar bites such as mixed cheese boards and charcuterie.
experiences.name: Dr. Fern's Gin Parlour

experiences.introduction: Ping Pong 129 Gintonería is a great hideaway after a long day. The Spanish Gin-tonic experience here is as relaxing as its laid-back and chic interiors. Not sure what to get? Try its G&T tasting.
experiences.name: Ping Pong 129 Gintonería

experiences.introduction: In collaboration with New York's Iconic cocktail bar 'PDT (Please Don't Tell), PDT Hong Kong is a bar within a bar. Expect intimacy and nothing but stellar cocktails. Just remember - mum's the word.
experiences.name: Please Don't Tell (PDT)

experiences.introduction: The Wilshire is one of the best speakeasies to visit that’s located within the Mexican restaurant 11 Westside. Tell the bartenders your drink preferences and they’ll shake up your custom cocktail.
experiences.name: The Wilshire

experiences.introduction: Fancy the rare bourbon Pappy van Winkle? Try to catch it at 001. Hidden in a black door, this speakeasy is concealed behind Graham Street’s market stalls. Just find that doorbell and dim spotlight.
A bar within a bar, Frank’s Library is the perfect place to enjoy premium cocktails that are inspired by fictional Frank Minza’s adventures. This speakeasy has a 1950s-style interior.
experiences.name: Frank's Library

experiences.introduction: The Poet is a secret drinking spot to enjoy house signature twists. Its Crimson Tide is scrumptiously spicy with a salty hint of nori from its gin base. Try also the lime-infused bourbon mix It Girl!
experiences.name: The Poet

experiences.introduction: If whisky is your drink of choice, go to Mizunara, a speakeasy where you’ll be greeted with more than 800 whisky bottles from Irish, Japanese, American, and Scottish distilleries. Try its cocktails!
experiences.name: Mizunara

experiences.introduction: A hidden pub serving creative cocktails? Head over to The Wise King which is hidden behind a discreet door in Staunton Street. Its Mandirino Negroni and Sherry Peach Collins are a must-try!
experiences.name: The Wise King

experiences.introduction: Knock knock. Check-in for a 5-star speak-easy exerpeince where creativity, curioisty and charm are the defining characteristics of the cocktails served up at Room 309. This one's a gem!
experiences.name: Room 309

experiences.introduction: If you’re looking for a sophisticated speakeasy spot that caters to women only, go to XX at Rosewood Hong Kong. Enjoy bite-sized snacks and light cocktails here with your lady friendships!
experiences.name: XX

experiences.introduction: Reward yourself with a glass of cocktail in The Old Man. Laid back and serene, this speakeasy is inspired by Ernest Hemingway's The Old Man and the Sea.  Its True at First Light is a must-try.
experiences.name: The Old Man

experiences.introduction: Foxglove proves that the best places are hidden in plain sight. This speakeasy presents itself as an umbrella shop on Duddell Street. Go towards the back of the boutique and find the entrance there.
experiences.name: Foxglove

experiences.introduction: If you’re into whisky, choose from Nocturne’s three sets of unique whisky tasting options. This Japanese-inspired speakeasy features dim lights and soft jazz for a more mysterious appeal.
experiences.name: Nocturne

experiences.introduction: Don't forget to unwind even on a hump day. Missy Ho's mocktails and mixes are funky enough to get you relaxed. If you're feeling more adventurous, try this speakeasy's CBD cocktails.
experiences.name: Missy Ho's

experiences.introduction: A whisky lover’s dream, Butler is a Japanese-inspired speakeasy that features an extensive cocktail and whisky menu. Watch the experts create your bespoke drink that’s based on your preferences.
experiences.name: Butler

experiences.introduction: A top choice for after-work drinks, where an effortlessly chic ambience meets classic American mixology. Our favourite drinks include the English House Punch and the Tarling!
experiences.name: The Diplomat

experiences.introduction: Duddell’s is known for making aesthetically pleasing dim sum dishes. Try its garoupa dumplings with spicy termite mushroom and shrimp arranged as a “fish pond” that’s too beautiful to eat.
experiences.name: Duddell’s

experiences.introduction: Man Wah’s not-so-extensive menu is a mark of this fine dining restaurant’s focus and innovation to its dishes. Wagyu beef puffs dim sum seasoned with black pepper sauce is a must-try!
experiences.name: Man Wah

experiences.introduction: Dim sum without the guilt? Try Dragon-I's Omnipork from its vegan menu. Made with plant-based proteins, shiitake mushroom, and non-GMO soy, Omnipork tastes like real pork without the meat!
experiences.name: Dragon-I

experiences.introduction: While Spring Moon’s dumplings are already sumptuous on their own, try these with its signature XO sauce for an added flavour. Minced pork and Sicilian red prawn dim sum are crowd favourites.
experiences.name: Spring Moon

experiences.introduction: A classic dim sum made with a modern spin? Don’t miss out on Mott 31’s siu mai with soft quail egg, black truffle, and Iberico pork. Its Shanghainese xiao long bao with caviar and crab is worth a try!
experiences.name: Mott 32

experiences.introduction: Lin Heung Tea is where you can get classic dim sum while appreciating what Hong Kong used to be. It’s an old-school trolly service so be sure to catch on to the servers before the dishes run out!
experiences.name: Lin Heung Tea

experiences.introduction: Man Ho prides itself on serving homemade dim sum. This acclaimed eatery offers steamed, pan-fried, baked, and deep-fried dim sum, so you have a lot of choices for your upcoming gathering.
experiences.name: Man Ho

experiences.introduction: Fancy a dim sum fix with a view of Victoria Harbour? Head on to Lung King Heen and have a taste of steamed scallop and lobster dumpling as well as the Racan pigeon dim sum with taro, to name a few.
experiences.name: Lung King Heen

experiences.introduction: Sheraton’s Celestial Court adds modern spins to classic dim sum through its famed har gow dish, which you can enjoy with Chinese tea. The restaurant’s signature shrimp dumplings are also worth a try.
experiences.name: Celestial Court

experiences.introduction: Seventh Son is known for its iconic dim sums such as steamed char siu buns and pork dumplings. If you want something sweet, try the upscale eatery’s glutinous dumpling with red bean paste
experiences.name: Seventh Son

experiences.introduction: Kin’s Kitchen sumptuous steamed dishes include meat and shrimp dumpling with truffle paste topping. Its sweet treats such as the water chestnut pudding and sesame rolls are worth a try.
experiences.name: Kin's Kitchen

collection_detail.introduction: You win sum, you dim sum!
collection_detail.name: Dim Sum Legends

experiences.introduction: Fresca makes eating healthy possible with its ready-to-go hot or cold meals. Grab a bite of the café's freshly made salads or create your own with the house special sauces.  All healthy choices!
experiences.name: Fresca

experiences.introduction: Looking to eat healthier at home? You'll love Greenwoods Cafe's sumptuous but guilt-free meals made with fresh and locally sourced ingredients. Its zucchini bolognese is a must-try!
experiences.name: Greenwoods Raw Cafe

experiences.introduction: If living a healthier lifestyle is your priority, do it with Kind Kitchen.  Try its spicy Italian spaghetti made with plant-based crab meat. This also comes with Buddhist-friendly option.
experiences.name: Kind Kitchen

experiences.introduction: Knead has just everything you need to get started with a healthier lifestyle. From offering a vegan sandwich to catering a group of health-conscious people, Knead's got you covered!
experiences.name: Knead

experiences.introduction: Who says healthy food must taste awful? Locofama offers healthy and organic dishes that are both nutritional and palatable. Its menu includes dairy-free, vegan, nut-free, and other healthy options.
experiences.name: Locofama

experiences.introduction: Loop Kulture is one of the places in Kowloon where you can get your clean-food fix.  Try its rainbow yogurt bowl as well as avocado and fig toast with salad and gelatoa.  Very apetising!
experiences.name: Loop Kulture

experiences.introduction: Sumptuous and healthy delights await you at Maison Libanaise. This all-day Lebanese canteen's menu highlights baked samké harra, chicken meshoué, eggplant moussaka, and roasted cauliflower.
experiences.name: Maison Libanaise

experiences.introduction: If you're a health-conscious and eco-conscious eater, try MANA! Its menu features options for various diet types and restrictions without compromising flavour. Grab an oven-baked za'atar flatbread!
experiences.name: Mana! Slow Fast Food - Central

experiences.introduction: If you're a health-conscious and eco-conscious eater, try MANA! Its menu features options for various diet types and restrictions without compromising flavour. Grab an oven-baked za'atar flatbread!
experiences.name: Mana! Slow Fast Food - Wan Chai

experiences.introduction: Nood Food ensures goodness and freshness in every bite with their grab-and-go fridges in multiple locations. From cold-pressed juices to sandwiches and more, you've got a lot of healthy choices here.
experiences.name: Nood Food - Central

experiences.introduction: Nood Food ensures goodness and freshness in every bite with their grab-and-go fridges in multiple locations. From cold-pressed juices to sandwiches and more, you've got a lot of healthy choices here.
experiences.name: Nood Food - Wan Chai

experiences.introduction: Nood Food ensures goodness and freshness in every bite with their grab-and-go fridges in multiple locations. From cold-pressed juices to sandwiches and more, you've got a lot of healthy choices here.
experiences.name: Nood Food - Quarry Bay

experiences.introduction: Nood Food ensures goodness and freshness in every bite with their grab-and-go fridges in multiple locations. From cold-pressed juices to sandwiches and more, you've got a lot of healthy choices here.
experiences.name: Nood Food - Admiralty

experiences.introduction: Fancy a healthy salad for lunch? Grab an Omega 3 Salad from OVO Cafe. This dish features sprouted walnuts, flax seeds, pumpkin seeds, cherry tomatoes, kale, and other mixed greens.
experiences.name: OVO Cafe

experiences.introduction: Want some guilt-free smoothie delight? Have a frozen treat from Supabowl which has no added sugar, no artificial ingredients, and no other hidden additives. Just pure, healthy goodness!
experiences.name: Supabowl - Central

experiences.introduction: Want some guilt-free smoothie delight? Have a frozen treat from Supabowl which has no added sugar, no artificial ingredients, and no other hidden additives. Just pure, healthy goodness!
experiences.name: Supabowl - Wan Chai

experiences.introduction: Treating your health-conscious friends or family to good food has been made easier with Tallore. Here, you have eight choices of salad trays. Kale, classic caesar, and more... take your pick!
experiences.name: Tallore

experiences.introduction: Customise your own healthy comfort food  at Treehouse. Here, the dishes are unprocessed and free from artificial and unhealthy ingredients. Its signature sourdough flatbreads are a must-try!
experiences.name: Treehouse

experiences.introduction: VEDA's vegetarian comfort food features a menu that brings together Eastern and Western cultures. For breakfast, try its overnight oats made with 1% dark organic chocolate and peanut butter.
experiences.name: Veda

experiences.introduction: Treat yourself to a 1% vegetarian Indonesian dish from Veggie SF. Its Trip to Bali is a must-try, featuring gado-gado salad, fried tofu, cashew, and coconut rice. Best partnered with avocado!
experiences.name: Veggie SF

collection_detail.introduction: Good health is at the root of it all
collection_detail.name: Healthy Eats
